---
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from "../consts";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

import { Content } from "../content/pages/index.md";
import EventsTable from "../components/EventsTable.astro";

const introText =
  "Welcome to our community space for those interested in the monastic path, supporting monastics in general, and the journey of Bhante Gunaviro in particular.";
---

<Layout
  title={SITE_TITLE}
  description={SITE_DESCRIPTION}
>
  <main class="space-y-6">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
      <img
        src="/static/bhante-1.png"
        alt="Bhante"
        class="h-36 w-full rounded-md border border-zinc-500/50 object-cover"
      />
      <img
        src="/static/bhante-2.png"
        alt="Leaf"
        class="h-36 w-full rounded-md border border-zinc-500/50 object-cover"
      />
    </div>
    <article class="space-y-6 text-base text-slate-700">
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-900">{introText}</p>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="lg:mx-[-100px]">
          <EventsTable />
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white p-5 shadow-md shadow-slate-200/70">
          <div class="space-y-5 text-sm text-slate-700">
            <div>
              <div class="mb-2 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
                <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-sky-50 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-sky-700 ring-1 ring-inset ring-sky-500/30">
                  Winter Retreat
                </span>
                <span class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">Nov 20 – Jan 17</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-base text-slate-700">
                During Winter Retreat, Bhante Gunaviro will not be available for drop-in hours or discussions after the
                meal. Dhamma talks will continue as scheduled.
                   <br />   <br />
                 If you are interested in making a meal offering during the retreat, please email
                <a class="font-semibold text-slate-900 underline-offset-2 hover:underline" href="mailto:samanasevana@gmail.com">
                  samanasevana@gmail.com</a>
                and a lay supporter can help find an appropriate time.
              </p>
            </div>
            <hr class="border-slate-200" />
             <div>
              <div class="mb-2 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
                <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-indigo-50 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-indigo-700 ring-1 ring-inset ring-indigo-500/30">
                  One-Day Meditation Retreat (Open to All)
                </span>
                <span class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">Nov 30</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-base text-slate-700">
Sunday, November 30, 2025 | 9:00 AM – 6:00 PM <br />
1135 Deana Court<br />
Morgan Hill, CA
<br /><br />
Dear Friends,<br />
We warmly invite you to join us for a one-day meditation retreat guided by Bhante Gunaviro. This is a rare and meaningful opportunity to practice in a peaceful and supportive environment with direct guidance from a monastic teacher.
<br /><br />
Throughout the day, Bhante will offer instructions on applying the Four Noble Truths and the Noble Eightfold Path to meditation practice and daily life.
<br /><br />
Participants who wish may also undertake the Eight Precepts for the day to deepen mindfulness, contentment, and restraint.
<br /><br />
<strong>Schedule</strong><br />
9:00 AM — Opening, Taking Refuge, Five Precepts / Eight Precepts<br />
10:30 AM — Meal Offering<br />
12:00 PM — Dhamma Talk<br />
<br />
Afternoon: Walking meditation and sitting meditation continue.<br />
Participants may alternate between walking and sitting every 30 minutes.<br />
<br />
4:30 PM — End-of-day sharing &amp; Q&amp;A<br />
6:00 PM — Closing<br />
<br />
<strong>Why Attend?</strong><br />
This retreat is an opportunity to:<br />
Slow down and return to your own breathing<br />
<br />
Settle, calm, and balance the mind<br />
<br />
Bring mindfulness together with insight into impermanence<br />
<br />
Let go of craving, clinging, and the deeper roots of suffering<br />
<br />
Practice with a supportive community of fellow meditators<br />
<br />
Receive direct guidance from Bhante Guṇavīro<br />
<br />
Whether you are brand new to meditation or have been practicing for many years, you are warmly welcome. Please come without worry or expectations.<br />
<br />
<strong>Please Bring:</strong><br />
Comfortable clothing<br />
A personal water bottle <br />
<br />
A mindful and open heart<br />
<br />
Everyone is welcome to attend.<br />
<br />
May this retreat help us cultivate clarity, peace, and liberation—for ourselves and for all beings.<br />
<br />
With metta,<br />
Mindful Yogis Group
              </p>
            </div>
            <hr class="border-slate-200" />
            <div>
              <div class="mb-2 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
                <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-amber-50 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-amber-700 ring-1 ring-inset ring-amber-400/30">
                  Dhamma Talk
                </span>
                <span class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">Lunar Observance Days</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-base text-slate-800">
                On Lunar Observance days, Bhante Gunaviro gives an hour-long Dhamma talk followed by Q&A. All are welcome.
                Please arrive on time to settle in before the talk begins.
              </p>
            </div>
            <hr class="border-slate-200" />
            <div>
              <div class="mb-2 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
                <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-emerald-700 ring-1 ring-inset ring-emerald-400/30">
                  Drop-In Hours
                </span>
                <span class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">See Schedule Above</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-base text-slate-700">
                Drop-In Hours are the best opportunity to meet with Bhante Gunaviro directly, ask Dhamma questions,
                offer support, or arrange meal offerings. Please refer to the schedule above for current Drop-In times.
              </p>
              <p class="mt-2 text-base text-slate-700">
                For more information, see the
                <a class="font-semibold text-slate-900 underline-offset-2 hover:underline" href="/support">
                  Support page</a>.
              </p>
            </div>
            <hr class="border-slate-200" />
            <div>
              <div class="mb-2 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2">
                <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-full bg-zinc-100 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wide text-zinc-700 ring-1 ring-inset ring-zinc-400/30">
                  WhatsApp Group
                </span>
               <span class="text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wide text-slate-500">Stay Connected</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-base text-slate-700">
                Our WhatsApp group is coordinated by the community for the benefit of all who wish to stay connected. If you'd like to join, please email 
                <a class="font-semibold text-slate-900 underline-offset-2 hover:underline" href="mailto:samanasevana@gmail.com">
                  samanasevana@gmail.com</a>.
                <br/>
                <br/>
                Please be aware that Bhante himself does not monitor this WhatsApp group or email — communications are organized by dedicated lay volunteers.
              </p>
            </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
